# Behaviour
- Confirm plan with user (SonuRam ji) before creating/merging major modules or DB migrations.
- Enforce: types, docs-sync, dependency-cycle check on every PR.

# Enforcements
- Every module directory MUST contain MODULE_DOC.md.
- Every file MUST include the Top-of-file header template (see .cursor/rules/header.template.mdc).
- Use structured logger (Pino) everywhere; console.debug only in non-prod gated blocks.
- Add requestId/correlation middleware to all HTTP & WebSocket flows.
- Update changelog in module doc after every edit.

# Changelog
- Every non-trivial change must add an entry to the relevant MODULE_DOC.md Change-log section (date, short description).
- For cross-cutting changes, add an entry to a root CHANGELOG.md if it exists.

# Dependency cycles
- PRs must pass `check:cycles` (madge). Modules may not depend on modules that depend back on them; shared code goes in `src/shared/` or `src/common/`.

# Manual actions
- Manual steps (DB migrate, duplicate check, codemods) are documented in manual_actions.mdc; run only after explicit approval or as part of release runbooks.
